deals.description: Adelis and four entrepreneurs form Circura, the leading group in renovation and service of properties. The new group becomes leading in the growing segment for renovation, rebuilding and service of properties.
Nordic BioSite Group, a distributor of life science products for research, brings in Adelis Equity Partners as new majority owner to accelerate growth and geographic expansion.
SSI Diagnostica acquires American CTK Biotech to create a leading global player in rapid diagnostics. The merger creates a strong global player in rapid patient-side diagnostics.

Provider of analysis services Red Ocean brings in Adelis Equity Partners as new majority owner. Red Ocean changes name to Kanari and aims for geographic expansion in stability and performance analysis of IT systems.
Adelis successfully exits Nordomatic AB, Nordic market leader in building automation and energy optimization, to Trill Impact. Revenue tripled from SEK 290M to SEK 880M during ownership.

Adelis invests in Axentia Technologies in partnership with company management to further accelerate growth through international expansion. Axentia is a leading provider of connected energy-efficient displays.
Adelis exits AddPro, one of Sweden's leading application and cloud integrators and IT outsourcing partners.
Adelis acquires majority of Didriksons shares from Herkules Capital. Didriksons is one of Scandinavia's leading brands for rain and functional clothing.
Adelis sells majority stake in IT Relation to Hg. IT Relation is the leading provider in the Danish managed IT services market with well over DKK 500 million in revenue.
Hantverksdata strengthens its ownership structure for faster expansion. Adelis becomes new majority owner to consolidate position as the leading ERP player in the Nordics for craft industries.
Habasit Group acquires majority stake in NGI Holding from Adelis. NGI's expertise in hygienic certified products enables Habasit to offer even broader solutions to customers.
Adelis successfully exits Med Group to Colosseum Dental Group and Tradeka consortium. Revenue more than doubled to €100 million during ownership period.
Søgemedier brings in Adelis as partner. Søgemedier is one of the leading players in digital marketing in Denmark with over 100 employees.
AddPro strengthens ownership structure for faster expansion. Adelis becomes new partner to continue developing the business and further increase growth.
EQT Growth invests €50 million in Harvey, a company specialized in AI solutions for legal and professional services, to support their international expansion.
EQT Real Estate completes sale of portfolio of seven logistics properties in the US, including facilities in Phoenix, Atlanta, Southern California and Texas.
Nordic Capital successfully lists NOBA, a leading European specialist bank operating under the Nordax Bank, Bank Norwegian and Svensk Hypotekspension brands, on Nasdaq Stockholm.
Summa Equity acquires majority stake in Nutris LLC, a sustainable plant-based nutrition factory based in Zagreb, Croatia, with research and development in Copenhagen, Denmark.
Summa Equity sells its shares in Olink Holding AB to Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc.
LEDiL, a company within the Ratos group, acquires Ingemann Components, a leading player in optical diffusers and reflective components in Northern Europe.
HENT, a company within the Ratos group, has been awarded a contract worth NOK 2.4 billion to build a new passenger terminal and several operational buildings at the new Bodø airport in Norway.

Litorina invests in Implema, Sweden's leading specialist in implementation of business systems SAP and Microsoft Dynamics. The company achieved 25% organic growth compared to the same period last year.
Empir Group acquires bonds and shares in ESSNSS AB from Litorina Kapital III L.P. with a total nominal amount of SEK 11,735,697 at a price of SEK 7,041,418.20.

Layer Group (Litorina portfolio company) acquires InDoor Floor & Wall Sweden AB, located in Kristinehamn. The company is a well-reputed business that performs multiple services within the floor segment, primarily tile laying and carpet laying in wet rooms.

Mästarna Vision AB, part of Layer Group (Litorina portfolio company), acquires Granlunds Måleri AB in Sundsvall. This acquisition strengthens Layer Group's painting services offering in Norrland and establishes presence in the Sundsvall region.

Layer Group (Litorina portfolio company) acquires Målerifixarna i Linköping AB, which has a strong position in its local market. This acquisition establishes Layer Group's presence in the Mälardalen area and strengthens the foundation for further expansion.

Verdane Intressenter holds approximately 97.1% of the shares and approximately 98.2% of the convertibles in Capilon after the final acceptance period. This represents a successful completion of the cash offer to shareholders and convertible holders.

NEO Energy, backed by HitecVision, acquires ExxonMobil's non-operated upstream assets in the British North Sea. The acquisition includes 40 oil and gas producing fields, enhancing production capacity and solidifying position in the UK Continental Shelf.

NEO Energy acquires Zennor Petroleum, increasing production from 80,000 barrels of oil equivalent per day in 2021 to approximately 100,000 boepd by 2026, reinforcing its status as a leading independent operator in the UK offshore oil and gas industry.
Verdane acquires Lumene, a Finnish cosmetics company, to support its international expansion and growth in the direct-to-consumer market.
Confirmit, backed by Verdane and Zobito, acquires FocusVision Worldwide to expand technology and service offerings in market and customer research.
Sval, backed by HitecVision, acquires Edison Norge, gaining 10 production licenses on the Norwegian Continental Shelf, diversifying its assets in the region.

Nordic Capital exits The Binding Site, a global leader in specialty diagnostics. Since acquisition in 2011, the company transformed into a leader in innovative medical solutions, growing fivefold with revenues of approximately GBP 200 million in 2022.
Nordic Capital acquires Sortera, a recycling and waste solutions firm, to support its expansion and growth in the recycling and waste management sector.
EQT acquires OX2, a Swedish wind power provider, as part of its strategy to invest in renewable energy sources and bolster its renewable energy portfolio.
KKR acquires Accountor, a Finnish software provider, from Vitruvian Partners to enhance its presence in the software sector.
Corten Capital acquires Roima Intelligence, a supply chain software company, from Intera Partners to expand its software solutions portfolio.

Summa Equity acquires Fortum's recycling and waste business to strengthen its position in the recycling and waste management sector, aligning with its focus on environmental sustainability investments.
